      <fr:mainmatter>
        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>534</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">sga1-i.5.5</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>sga1-i.5.5.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
            <fr:authors />
            <fr:number>I.5.5</fr:number>
            <fr:parent>sga1-i.5</fr:parent>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> be a prescheme, and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex> be <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>-preschemes.
    Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S_0]]></fr:tex> be a closed sub-prescheme of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> that has the same underlying space as <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>, and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X_0=X\times _S S_0]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y_0=Y\times _S S_0]]></fr:tex> be the "restrictions" of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S_0]]></fr:tex>.
    Suppose that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is étale over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>.
    Then the natural map
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Hom}_S(Y,X) \to  \operatorname {Hom}_{S_0}(X_0,Y_0)]]></fr:tex>
    is <fr:em>bijective</fr:em>.</fr:p>
  
    
    <fr:tree toc="false" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>480</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">#258</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-258.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:parent>sga1-i.5.5</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>We can again reduce to the case where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y=S]]></fr:tex>, and then this follows from the "topological" description of sections of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X/Y]]></fr:tex> given in <fr:ref addr="sga1-i.5.3" href="sga1-i.5.3.xml" taxon="Corollary" number="I.5.3" />.</fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
  
</fr:mainmatter>
